 dad died of lung cancer when I was a freshman in high school.  Your children and wife are so lucky that you had your epiphany not only when you did but that you are making a conscious effort not to be selfish now.  It will mean the world to them later.</p><span id='bc_0_23MN' class='comment-actions secondary-text' kind='m'><a kind='i' href='javascript:;' target='_self' o='r'>Reply</a><span class='item-control blog-admin pid-1660424148'><a o='d' target='_self' href='http://www.blogger.com/delete-comment.g?blogID=6389679439326917475&amp;postID=859726085869878707'>Delete</a></span></span></div><div id='bc_0_23BR' class='comment-replies'></div><div id='bc_0_23B_box' class='comment-replybox-single'></div></li><li id='bc_0_24B' class='comment' kind='b'><div class='avatar-image-container'><img src='http://img1.blogblog.com/img/anon36.png'></img></div><div id='c5501426741242733720' class='comment-block'><div id='bc_0_24M' class='comment-header' kind='m'><cite class='user'><a rel='nofollow' href='http://www.scarymommy.com/double-digits/'>Scary Mommy</a></cite><span class='icon user'></span><span class='datetime secondary-text'><a rel='nofollow' href='http://www.bloggerfather.com/2014/06/cancer.html?showComment=1401807219935&amp;m=1#c5501426741242733720'>June 3, 2014 at 10:53 AM</a></span></div><p id='bc_0_24MC' class='comment-content'>Oh, Oren, I don&#39;t even know what to say, but I am so glad you had that moment on the ride home. Your family is so blessed to have you.</p><span id='bc_0_24MN' class='comment-actions secondary-text' kind='m'><a kind='i' href='javascript:;' target='_self' o='r'>Reply</a><span class='item-control blog-admin pid-736295364'><a o='d' target='_self' href='http://www.blogger.com/delete-comment.g?blogID=6389679439326917475&amp;postID=5501426741242733720'>Delete</a></span></span></div><div id='bc_0_24BR' class='comment-replies'></div><div id='bc_0_24B_box' class='comment-replybox-single'></div></li><li id='bc_0_25B' class='comment' kind='b'><div cla